{"id":"moltinger-6ql","title":"Implement SearXNG self-hosted web search as fallback","description":"## Context\n\nBrave Search now requires credit card (not truly free).\nTavily provides 1,000 free requests/month via MCP server.\n\n## Goal\n\nDeploy SearXNG as self-hosted metasearch engine on ainetic.tech server for unlimited, completely free web search.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Deploy SearXNG via Docker Compose on same server as Moltis\n- Configure as MCP server or HTTP endpoint for Moltis\n- Aggregate multiple search engines (Google, Bing, DuckDuckGo, etc.)\n- No rate limits, no API keys, no credit card\n\n## Technical Notes\n\n- SearXNG GitHub: https://github.com/searxng/searxng\n- Can be added to docker-compose.prod.yml alongside Moltis\n- Expose on internal port, integrate via MCP or custom tool\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] SearXNG container running on ainetic.tech\n- [ ] Web search working through SearXNG\n- [ ] Fallback from Tavily when rate limited\n- [ ] Documentation updated","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"s060874@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-02-17T12:56:23.639155+03:00","created_by":"Сергей Кружилин","updated_at":"2026-02-17T12:56:39.903664+03:00","labels":["free-tier","infrastructure","web-search"]}
{"id":"moltinger-lzy","title":"BUG: Hardcoded ElevenLabs API keys in git-tracked files","description":"Two files contain exposed ElevenLabs API key: config/moltis.toml.backup and docs/plans/parallel-doodling-coral.md. IMMEDIATE: Rotate keys at elevenlabs.io, then remove/redact files.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"s060874@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-02-17T15:52:46.283858+03:00","created_by":"Сергей Кружилин","updated_at":"2026-02-17T16:07:57.108926+03:00","closed_at":"2026-02-17T16:07:57.108926+03:00","close_reason":"Fixed: Removed moltis.toml.backup, redacted keys from plan doc, added secrets/ to .gitignore","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"moltinger-lzy","depends_on_id":"moltinger-wisp-kvg","type":"discovered-from","created_at":"2026-02-17T15:52:46.285056+03:00","created_by":"Сергей Кружилин"}]}
{"id":"moltinger-pmc","title":"BUG: Telegram bot not responding","description":"Telegram bot configured but not responding to messages.\\n\\nPotential causes:\\n1. No 'enabled = true' in [channels.telegram] section\\n2. allowed_users commented out\\n3. Environment variables may not be loaded\\n\\nNeed to verify:\\n- TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN env var is set on server\\n- Bot token is valid (curl api.telegram.org/getMe)\\n- Moltis logs show Telegram initialization","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"s060874@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-02-17T16:22:38.928777+03:00","created_by":"Сергей Кружилин","updated_at":"2026-02-17T16:26:26.900491+03:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"moltinger-pmc","depends_on_id":"moltinger-wisp-kvg","type":"discovered-from","created_at":"2026-02-17T16:22:38.929779+03:00","created_by":"Сергей Кружилин"}]}
